{{define "impl_test_infra"}}
1. Look for `test` blocks in source files
2. Look for a `tests/` directory with integration tests
3. Look for existing test helper functions

When writing tests:
- Use `std.testing.allocator` to detect memory leaks
- Use `std.testing.expect*` functions for assertions
- Group related tests in the same file near the code they test
- For external dependencies, prefer comptime interfaces + test doubles
- Never mock what you don't own — wrap external dependencies in an interface first
{{- end}}

